  <h3 style="font-family:'Playfair Display',serif;color:var(--navy);margin-bottom:1rem;font-size:1.3rem;">What is a Short Strategy?</h3>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="info-box">
      <h4>Shorting a Stock — Plain Language</h4>
      <p>Shorting is a way to profit when a stock goes down. You borrow shares, sell them at today's price, and buy them back later at a lower price — pocketing the difference. If Riverdale shorts an auto company at $50 today and a recall drops that stock to $38, Riverdale keeps the $12 difference per share. The key is timing — the earlier you enter the short, the more of that decline you capture. That is exactly what our model gives Riverdale: the earliest possible entry, before anyone else knows a recall is coming.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-box">
