<div class="container section-pad">
  <span class="section-label">Stage 2 — Position Sizing</span>
  <h2 class="section-title">Kelly Criterion — Optimal Capital Allocation</h2>
  <p class="section-desc">A mathematical formula developed by John Kelly at Bell Labs (1956), applied to financial markets by Edward Thorp. Widely used by professional traders and hedge funds to determine the optimal position size given a known win rate and payoff. Not to be confused with Kelly Blue Book.</p>

  <div class="kelly-equation">
    <span class="eq-label">Full Kelly Formula</span>
    <div class="eq-full">f* = (p × b − q) / b</div>
    <div class="eq-simple">f* = optimal fraction | p = win probability | b = win size / stop loss | q = 1 − p</div>
    <div style="margin-top:1rem;padding-top:1rem;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);">
      <span class="eq-label">In Simple Terms</span>
      <div style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-size:0.95rem;">Position = (how often it works × how much you make) minus (how often it fails × your stop loss)</div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top:1rem;padding-top:1rem;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1);">
      <span class="eq-label">Position Scaling Formula</span>
      <div class="eq-full" style="font-size:1.1rem;">Final Position = Base × (Signal Probability / Threshold)</div>
      <div class="eq-simple">Capped at $1,000,000 (10% of AUM) | Floored at $50,000 (0.5% of AUM)</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="kelly-vars">
    <div class="kelly-var"><div class="kv-sym">p — Win Rate</div><div class="kv-desc">From Recall Impact Scorecard — how often this company's stock drops more than 2% on recall days</div><div class="kv-val">Base rate: 21.9% across all 3,631 recall events</div></div>
    <div class="kelly-var"><div class="kv-sym">b — Win Size</div><div class="kv-desc">Average drop size divided by stop loss. Bigger drops = better risk/reward ratio</div><div class="kv-val">Example — Lucid: -11.66% avg drop → positive Kelly → $604,000 base position</div></div>
    <div class="kelly-var"><div class="kv-sym">q — Loss Rate (1−p)</div><div class="kv-desc">How often the stock does NOT drop and the short loses to the stop loss</div><div class="kv-val">Stop loss fixed at 5% — maximum loss per trade before exit</div></div>
    <div class="kelly-var"><div class="kv-sym">Half-Kelly Applied</div><div class="kv-desc">We use half the Kelly fraction (f*/2) to account for estimation error and reduce volatility</div><div class="kv-val">Standard institutional practice for Kelly Criterion deployment</div></div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid-2" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
    <div class="info-box">
      <h4>Portfolio Parameters</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Portfolio size:</strong> $10,000,000 — consistent with emerging manager AUM per The Hedge Fund Journal (2023)</li>
